SIMPLE: lightness
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lightness
<hw>Light"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Light</er> not
heavy.]</ety> <def>The state, condition, or quality, of being light or
not heavy; buoyancy; levity; fickleness; nimbleness; delicacy;
grace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Levity; volatility; instability; inconstancy;
unsteadiness; giddiness; flightiness; airiness; gayety; liveliness;
agility; nimbleness; sprightliness; briskness; swiftness; ease;
facility.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lightness</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lightness
<hw>Light"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Light</er>
bright.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Illumination, or degree of illumination;
<as>as, the <ex>lightness</ex> of a room</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Absence of depth or of duskiness in color; <as>as,
the <ex>lightness</ex> of a tint; <ex>lightness</ex> of
complexion.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lightning</ent>⟦br⟧
